00:48:13.810 --> 00:48:20.020
projects, people skimming off the top because
that's the nature in places like this, and

00:48:20.020 --> 00:48:23.270
I'm sure that's the nature in big IT projects
all over the world. There's always someone

00:48:23.270 --> 00:48:24.270
skimming off the top.

00:48:24.270 --> 00:48:31.551
But at the same time, if it increases transparency,
which is what it's doing and if reduces corruption

00:48:31.551 --> 00:48:37.550
and bureaucracy because it reduces that distance
between the person and the government and

00:48:37.550 --> 00:48:42.619
the modes for those people to come in and
become middlemen -- which they had before

00:48:42.619 --> 00:48:49.050
and because of the Internet can't -- then
I think it will at least go some way to solving

00:48:49.050 --> 00:48:50.560
that problem for sure.

