00:50:55.859 --> 00:51:00.400
since India is not known for research. So
even if you did stay on, the facilities are

00:51:00.400 --> 00:51:04.339
so poor and the resources are so poor that
you couldn't really make a mark. But that

00:51:04.339 --> 00:51:10.280
is changing. So for example at IIT Delhi,
they're introducing programs now which will

00:51:10.280 --> 00:51:16.369
help you get funding, if not from the government
or from the college then from private sources.

00:51:16.369 --> 00:51:21.099
And providing these kinds of incentives for
students to stay on and do Ph.D.'s. I really

00:51:21.099 --> 00:51:26.790
hope that happens because that's what you
need to build a truly scientific country and

00:51:26.790 --> 00:51:31.320
that's where has India suffered all these
great undergraduates go to the U.S. and do

00:51:31.320 --> 00:51:38.750
their Ph.D.'s here and contribute to America's
scientific society and not to India's. But

00:51:38.750 --> 00:51:42.270
